claims:
25. A method of identifying an anti-infective compound, the method comprising:
(a) providing first and second subsets of cells;
(b) infecting the first and second subsets of cells with a marker-producing bacteria;
(c) staining the first subset of cells with a vitality marker and obtaining a first value of cellular infectivity;
(d) contacting the second subset of cells with an anti-infective compound; and
(e) staining the second subset of cells with a vitality marker and obtaining a second value of cellular infectivity; wherein when the second value of cellular infectivity is decreased compared to the first value of cellular infectivity, an anti-infective compound is identified.
